cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.BI, cs.RO, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of P. polycephalum as a computing substrate, which falls under the category of neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.NE). The introduction of artificial circuit components into the plasmodium also involves the study of electrical properties and engineering of electronic devices, which falls under the category of electronics (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the bioelectrical activity of the plasmodium and its information processing capabilities, which falls under the category of bioinformatics (cs.BI). The use of hybridised slime mould to form biomorphic mineralised networks and facilitate the transmission of electricity involves the study of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for producing functional unconventional computing devices using hybridised slime mould, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
